

Console (Azure Portal) Solution
To add the tag via the Azure Portal, follow these steps:
Go to the Azure Portal: Open Azure Portal.
Navigate to the Virtual Machine:
In the left-hand navigation pane, search for "Virtual machines" and select it.
Click on the nautilus-vm virtual machine.
Go to the Tags Section:
In the Overview page of the virtual machine, under the Settings section, click on Tags.
Add the Tag:
In the Tags blade, click on + Add tag.
In the Name field, type Environment, and in the Value field, type dev.
Click Save to apply the tag.

CLI Solution
To add a tag Environment=dev to the virtual machine nautilus-vm, you can use the following command:
az vm update \
  --resource-group <your-resource-group> \
  --name nautilus-vm \
  --set tags.Environment=dev

~ âžœ  az vm show \
